## The 25 Most Common Mistakes

<div class="my-8">

### **Platform Selection Mistakes**

<div class="my-6 p-6 bg-rose-50 border-l-4 border-rose-500">

#### **Mistake #1: Choosing Without Research**

**THE PROBLEM:** 41% of users choose first platform they find without alternatives.

**CONSEQUENCE:**
- Platform lock-in (can't leave easily)
- Wrong features for their needs
- Overpaying for unnecessary features
- Template saturation (looks like everyone else)

**THE FIX:**
- Research 3-5 platforms before choosing
- Compare features important to YOU
- Read recent reviews (Reddit, Trustpilot)
- Test free trials thoroughly
- Check if code export available (in case you want to leave)

</div>

---

<div class="my-6 p-6 bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500">

#### **Mistake #2: Ignoring Lock-In**

**THE PROBLEM:** 67% of users don't check if they can export their site/content.

**CONSEQUENCE:**
- Trapped on platform forever
- Expensive to rebuild ($5,000-25,000)
- SEO loss if migrate (30-60% traffic drop)
- Platform holds your content hostage

**THE FIX:**
- Check if code export available before choosing
- Test data export (CSV/API)
- Read cancellation policy
- Understand migration difficulty
- **Platforms with code export:** Webflow, Framer, WordPress

</div>

---

<div class="my-6 p-6 bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-500">

#### **Mistake #3: Falling for "2-Minute Website" Claims**

**THE PROBLEM:** Marketing claims vs reality. AI generates basic frame, not finished site.

**CONSEQUENCE:**
- Unrealistic expectations
- Disappointment with results
- Still requires hours of manual work
- "2 minutes" becomes 2 days

**THE FIX:**
- Expect 2-8 hours for professional site
- AI creates frame, you add polish
- Quality takes time (always)
- Budget for content creation

</div>

---

### **Content Mistakes**

<div class="my-6 p-6 bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500">

#### **Mistake #4: Letting AI Write All Your Copy**

**THE PROBLEM:** AI-generated content is generic and sounds robotic.

**CONSEQUENCE:**
- Low conversion (0.5-1% vs 2-5%)
- No brand personality
- Doesn't connect with audience
- Sounds like everyone else

**THE FIX:**
- Use AI for outline and structure
- Write your own headlines and CTAs
- Add your voice and personality
- Be specific, not vague
- Test different messages

</div>

---

<div class="my-6 p-6 bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500">

#### **Mistake #5: Vague Value Propositions**

**THE PROBLEM:** "The best way to X" means nothing to visitors.

**CONSEQUENCE:**
- High bounce rate (60-80%)
- Low engagement
- No conversions
- Wasted traffic

**THE FIX:**
- Be specific: "Save 10 hours/week" not "Save time"
- Use numbers and data
- Focus on benefits, not features
- Speak customer language
- Test clarity vs cleverness (clarity wins)

</div>

---

<div class="my-6 p-6 bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-500">

#### **Mistake #6: No Clear CTA**

**THE PROBLEM:** 67% of AI-built sites lack clear next step for visitors.

**CONSEQUENCE:**
- Visitors don't know what to do
- Leave without engaging
- Conversion rate: 0.1-0.5%

**THE FIX:**
- One clear CTA above fold
- Repeat CTAs throughout page
- Make it specific: "Start Free" not "Learn More"
- Button design stands out
- Remove navigation links initially (single-focus)

</div>

---

### **Design Mistakes**

<div class="my-6 p-6 bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500">

#### **Mistake #7: Using AI-Generated Templates As-Is**

**THE PROBLEM:** 78% of AI sites use 1 of 12 templates.

**CONSEQUENCE:**
- Looks like everyone else
- No brand differentiation
- Low trust and credibility
- Generic appearance

**THE FIX:**
- Start from blank canvas when possible
- Customize colors, fonts, layouts
- Add your brand elements
- Make it uniquely yours
- Consider design-focused platforms (Framer, Webflow)

</div>

---

<div class="my-6 p-6 bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500">

#### **Mistake #8: Ignoring Mobile Optimization**

**THE PROBLEM:** 40-60% of traffic is mobile, many sites not optimized.

**CONSEQUENCE:**
- High bounce rate on mobile (70-90%)
- Low conversion from mobile
- Poor user experience
- Google penalizes in rankings

**THE FIX:**
- Test on real phones (not just browser tools)
- Large, tappable buttons
- Readable without zooming
- Fast load time (&lt;3s on mobile)
- Simplify navigation for mobile

</div>

---

<div class="my-6 p-6 bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-500">

#### **Mistake #9: Poor Image Quality**

**THE PROBLEM:** AI compresses images, destroying quality.

**CONSEQUENCE:**
- Unprofessional appearance
- Low trust
- Doesn't showcase work properly
- Color accuracy loss

**THE FIX:**
- Manually optimize before upload
- Use 90%+ quality for important images
- 2,500px+ width for full-screen
- Test on retina displays
- Lazy load below-fold images manually

</div>

---

### **Technical Mistakes**

<div class="my-6 p-6 bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500">

#### **Mistake #10: Not Testing Before Launch**

**THE PROBLEM:** 53% of users publish without thorough testing.

**CONSEQUENCE:**
- Broken forms
- Typos and errors
- Mobile issues
- Lost leads and credibility

**THE FIX:**
- Test contact form (send real test)
- Test on multiple devices
- Test in multiple browsers
- Have others review before launch
- Check all links work

</div>

---

<div class="my-6 p-6 bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500">

#### **Mistake #11: Slow Page Speed**

**THE PROBLEM:** Many AI sites load in 5-10 seconds.

**CONSEQUENCE:**
- High bounce rate (70-90% leave)
- Poor Google rankings
- Lost conversions
- Frustrating user experience

**THE FIX:**
- Compress images before upload
- Limit video embeds
- Minimize plugins/apps
- Use platform's speed optimization
- Test with Google PageSpeed Insights

</div>

---

<div class="my-6 p-6 bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-500">

#### **Mistake #12: No Analytics Installed**

**THE PROBLEM:** 61% of sites don't track visitor behavior.

**CONSEQUENCE:**
- No data to improve
- Don't know what's working
- Can't optimize conversion
- Flying blind

**THE FIX:**
- Install Google Analytics 4 immediately
- Set up conversion tracking
- Monitor weekly at minimum
- Use data to guide improvements
- A/B test based on data

</div>

